    <briefdescription>
<para>Base <ref refid="classCommand" kindref="compound">Command</ref> class with flexible dict-based parameters. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This class uses nanobind::dict for maximum flexibility and seamless Python interop. Parameters can be of any type that nanobind supports.</para>
<para>Usage Example (C++): <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="classCommand" kindref="compound">Command</ref><sp/>cmd(</highlight><highlight class="stringliteral">&quot;drop_to_world&quot;</highlight><highlight class="normal">);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">cmd[</highlight><highlight class="stringliteral">&quot;item_index&quot;</highlight><highlight class="normal">]<sp/>=<sp/>5;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">cmd[</highlight><highlight class="stringliteral">&quot;world_x&quot;</highlight><highlight class="normal">]<sp/>=<sp/>100.0f;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="keywordtype">int</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>index<sp/>=<sp/>nb::cast&lt;int&gt;(cmd[</highlight><highlight class="stringliteral">&quot;item_index&quot;</highlight><highlight class="normal">]);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Usage Example (Python): <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal">cmd<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="classCommand_1a18df2d81039392daeb0b78c346a70537" kindref="member">Command</ref>(</highlight><highlight class="stringliteral">&quot;drop_to_world&quot;</highlight><highlight class="normal">)</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">cmd[&quot;item_index&quot;]<sp/>=<sp/>5</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">cmd[&quot;world_x&quot;]<sp/>=<sp/>100.0</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">index<sp/>=<sp/>cmd[&quot;item_index&quot;]</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para>
    </detaileddescription>
